<TEXT>
here is a chronology of major events in the nancy cruzan 
righttodie case 
jan 11 1983 nancy cruzan then 25 has a wreck on a country 
road southeast of carthage in the ozarks of southwest missouri and 
is thrown from the car paramedics restart her breathing but her 
brain was without oxygen for so long she never regains 
consciousness 
feb 5 1983 doctors implant a feeding tube in ms cruzans 
stomach she isnt on any life support system such as a 
respirator 
oct 19 1983 ms cruzan is moved to the missouri 
rehabilitation center in mount vernon where she remains 
oct 23 1987 her parents joe and joyce cruzan of carterville 
ask jasper county probate judge charles teel for a judgment on 
their request that they be allowed to have ms cruzans feeding 
tube removed so she can die as they believe she would want 
march 9 1988 a threeday hearing begins on the familys 
request the cruzans say their daughter has a commonlaw right to 
be free from unwanted medical treatment and state and federal 
constitutional rights to privacy that protect her right to refuse 
unwanted medical treatment 
july 27 1988 teel issues a judgment authorizing the cruzans 
acting as nancys legal guardians to request the withholding of 
food and water from their daughter 
aug 3 1988 missouri attorney general william webster files 
notice that the state will appeal to the state supreme court 
sept 29 1988 the court hears arguments 
nov 16 1988 in a 43 decision the state supreme court 
overturns the lower court holding there is no legal authority to 
grant the cruzans request the family appeals to the us supreme 
court 
dec 6 1989 the us supreme court hears arguments the first 
time it has considered a righttodie case 
june 25 1990 in a 54 decision the court blocks the cruzans 
from halting their daughters food and water it says the state 
could keep a patient on life support in the absence of clear and 
convincing evidence the person would want to die 
aug 30 1990 ms cruzans parents ask teel for a second 
hearing saying they have new evidence their daughter once 
indicated to three people she would rather die than live in her 
present condition 
sept 17 1990 webster saying the state no longer has a 
recognizable legal interest in the case asks the judge to drop 
the state health department and the director of the missouri 
rehabilitation center from future litigation 
oct 23 1990 teel drops the state as a defendant leaving the 
parents and courtappointed guardian thad mccanse in the case 
nov 1 1990 three former coworkers tell teel they recalled 
conversations with ms cruzan in which she said she never would 
want to live like a vegetable on medical machines ms cruzans 
physician who previously opposed removing the feeding tube terms 
her life a living hell and testifies she should be allowed to 
die 
dec 5 1990 ms cruzans courtappointed guardians recommend 
the feeding tube be removed so ms cruzan may die 
dec 14 1990 teel authorizes removal of feeding tubes 
</TEXT>
