here are some facts and figures on albania 
 
the land albania covers 10600 square miles and is slightly 
larger than maryland it is in southeastern europe on the coast of 
the adriatic sea and its neighbors are yugoslavia and greece 
 
the people albanias 32 million people are made up primarly 
of the geg ethnic group in the north and the tosks in the south 
ethnic greeks make up about 25 percent of the populace 
 
the economy the chief industries of the country are mining 
chemical fertilizer and textiles its chief crops are corn wheat 
cotton potatoes tobacco citrus fruits and grapes 
 
the government albania is last remaining stalinist republic in 
eastern europe the communistrun peoples assembly a 
singlechamber legislature of 250 deputies meets a few days a year 
essentially to ratify actions taken in its name by the presidium of 
the assembly the presidium is led by ramiz alia the head of state 
and communist party leader 
on tuesday the party agreed to permit alternative political 
organizations and one day later the countrys first noncommunist 
party the democratic party of albania was founded 
new parliamentary elections are scheduled for feb 10 
</TEXT>
