<DOCNO> AP901214-0019 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here is a list of major political developments in albania 
 
1945 elections are held based on a single slate of candidates 
sponsored by the communists headed by enver hoxha 
1946 king zog is deposed and the peoples republic of albania 
is proclaimed 
1949 albania seeking protection from yugoslav expansionism 
joins the moscowbased cmea council for mutual economic 
assistance or comecon 
1955 albania joins the sovietled warsaw pact military 
alliance 
1961 the soviet union denounces albanias ties with beijing 
and breaks off relations 
1962 albania withdraws from the cmea and turns increasingly to 
china for support 
1968 albania withdraws from the warsaw pact 
1972 following the improvement of uschina relations 
albania becomes disenchanted with beijing 
1978 beijing formally terminates all economic and military 
support 
1982 the government stops an attempted coup by a group of 
albanian exiles the pretender to the throne while not directly 
involved admits knowing the rebels leader 
1985 enver hoxha dies and is replaced by ramiz alia who vows 
to continue hoxhas policies 
1987 alia reelected as president of the presidium and head of 
the party of labor of albania communist party 
1989 alia resists the reforms sweeping away the repressive 
communist leaderships in eastern europe and refuses to relinquish 
the communist partys constitutional monopoly on power 
1990 may communist leaders begin announcing cautious 
political economic and foreign policy reforms and signal 
willingness to reestablish ties with washington and moscow the 
reforms include liberalized travel the lifting of a ban on 
religious propaganda and the abolition of the death penalty for 
defectors 
july thousands of albanians storm foreign embassies and refuse 
to leave until they are granted permission to emigrate albania and 
the soviet union reestablish diplomatic ties 
october balkan foreign ministers hold a meeting in tirana the 
countrys leading writer ismail kadare defects while in france 
november parliament adopts legislation to allow independent 
candidates to stand in secret ballot elections 
dec 11 the communist party says it will allow noncommunist 
political parties to form 
dec 12 students and others found the first alternative party 
called the democratic party of albania 
dec 13 police and troops move to put down rioting 
hooligans in the northern city of shkodra 
</TEXT>
