a 750 million mission to study the 
suns poles is in danger because the ulysses spacecraft is wobbling 
for reasons us and european flight controllers dont fully 
understand 
the malfunction developed nov 4 about four weeks after the 
spacecraft was launched by the shuttle discovery the associated 
press has learned the spacecraft was 406 million miles from earth 
today 
officials of nasa and the european space agency confirmed the 
problems existence during interviews this week 
