situation 
natsios said 12 million tons of food will be needed to feed a 
third of the nation in 1991 of that amount only about 200000 
tons has been pledged by donor nations all of sudan apart from 
some eastern regions has been struck by two years of drought 
people already have begun moving to sudans capital khartoum 
from the most seriously effected regions and are forming feeding 
camps said rich machmer the head of the us international agency 
for development aid office in khartoum 
many of the estimated 1 million people who died in the 198485 
