alfred dennis sieminski a onetime democratic 
member of congress from new jersey who served as an army officer in 
world war ii and korea died thursday he was 79 
friends said sieminski collapsed and died while attending the 
annual christmas party of the mclean va kiwanis club he was a 
resident of the nearby suburb of vienna 
a native of jersey city nj and a 1934 graduate of princeton 
university sieminski also studied at hamburg uuniversity in 
germany the university of warsaw and harvard university law 
school 
at princeton he was a member of the university boxing team and 
was a member of the princeton crew which raced at the henley 
regatta in england 
