private he ended the war as a captain in the military government 
division in austria after service in the italian campaign he was 
discharged to the infantry reserve as a major in 1950 and promoted 
to lieutenant colonel in the reserves in 1956 
sieminski was elected to congress in 1951 he won reelection 
three times but was an unsuccessful candidate for renomination in 
1958 
