<TEXT>
friedrich duerrenmatt the swiss 
writer whose plays display a sardonic mix of realism and absurd 
visions died friday of heart failure he was 69 
the author of the visit and the physicists died at his 
home in the lakeside town of neuchatel in western switzerland the 
diogenes publishing house announced it was three weeks before his 
70th birthday 
duerrenmatts collected works comprise more than 30 volumes and 
have been translated from the german into over 50 languages he is 
believed to have been the most widely played contemporary dramatist 
since bertolt brecht 
besides plays duerrenmatt also wrote novels essays and his 
convoluted stoffe or materials which blend fiction with 
autobiographical notes his worldwide reputation was established by 
the visit which premiered in 1955 in the play an entire town 
slowly yields to the temptation of murdering one of its citizens 
for the sake of a promised fortune 
in another popular play the physicists first performed in 
1961 the main characters escape nuclear age realities in a 
madhouse 
his novels included justice which has a complicated murder 
plot his paintings also won considerable attention at several 
exhibitions 
duerrenmatts last play was titled achterloo a farcical 
theateroftheabsurd parable inspired by the martial law clampdown 
on polands solidarity movement it premiered in 1983 
he said the play tried to show that the modern world is 
changing into a theaterthe consequences will be disastrous 
the son of a protestant pastor duerrenmatt was born jan 5 
1921 at konolfingen a town near the swiss capital of bern 
originally he wanted to become a painter and also studied 
theology philosophy literature and natural sciences 
his first success as writer came in 1949 with romulus the 
great which he called an unhistorical historical comedy 
about the fall of the roman empire 
gloom mingled typically with impish irony and jocular paradoxes 
in duerrenmatts parabletype plays which he preferred to call 
comedies despite their tragic quality 
tragedy he once observed could no longer be written because 
the modern world lacking established standards of guilt and 
retribution was not suited for it 
the world he said stands as an enigma of calamity that has 
to be accepted but to which there must be no surrender 
several plays were turned into movies including the visit 
starring ingrid bergman and anthony quinn 
deurrenmatt suffered from a heart condition for more than 20 
years and was a diabetic funeral arrangements were not immediately 
known 
he is survived by his second wife charlotte a german tv 
director and writer whom he married in 1984 his first wife 
lotti and mother of his three children peter barbara and ruth 
died in early 1983 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

