were going back to work immediately said bernard 
adelstein leader of teamsters local 813 
under the deal the lowestpaid sanitation workers will get an 
increase of 125 percent over three years adelstein said a 
15aweek raise kicks in june 1 1991 30aweek raises will 
follow dec 1 1991 and dec 1 1992 he said 
the union set up picket lines sunday night after rejecting an 
offer that raised salaries 70 a week over three years the union 
sought a 90 increase in a threeyear contract 
the workers earn 600 to 700 a week under the old contract 
union leaders reached a tentative settlement thursday during a 
sevenhour session with city officials a spokesman for management 
did not return telephone messages left friday 
besides better wages the unions want private carters to pay a 
fee for using outofstate workers to haul trash to outofstate 
dumps the companies agreed the union would have the right to 
organize any such workers 
