590 million cash tender offer by the german energy and chemical 
company rwedea 
rwedea will offer to buy all of vistas outstanding common 
shares for 55 per share according to a definitive agreement 
signed by both companies 
the tender offer will begin by next wednesday they said 
this merger agreement which was consummated on an entirely 
friendly basis not only provides the best value for vista 
shareholders but also represents a sound and exciting future for 
our employees john d burns vistas chairman president and 
chief executive officer said thursday 
burns said that as part of the rwe group vista will be able 
to implement all appropriate investment projects designed to 
strengthen and enhance our joint operations 
houstonbased vista produces commodity and specialty chemicals 
used in a variety of products such as household laundry detergents 
shampoos cosmetics automobile trim and fittings vinyl packaging 
materials home siding and wire and cable coatings 
vistas earned 633 million for the 1990 year ending sept 30 
on sales of 719 million the company formed in 1984 has about 
1850 employees and owns or leases nine principal manufacturing and 
production facilities 
rwedea formerly known as deutsche texaco ag is involved in 
oil refining marketing exploration and production of oil and 
natural gas either directly or through subsidiaries the 
hamburgbased company which has about 6200 employees also 
manufactures a wide range of petrochemical basics and chemical 
products 
for the fiscal year ending dec 31 1989 rwedea had a net 
income of 120 million 
rwedea is an independent operating subsidiary of rwe ag a 
publicly held holding company that is involved in electricity 
mining oil and chemicals machinery construction and waste 
management through its six subsidiaries rwe ag owns more than 99 
percent ot rwedeas stock 
the combination of vista and rwedea provides a unique 
opportunity to expand significantly into the global chemicals 
market said armin schram rwedeas chairman 
we do not anticipate that the transaction will result in any 
significant changes in vistas structure of operation he said 
adding that no layoffs are anticipated and vista plans to keep its 
corporate headquarters in houston 
the 590 million offer is expected to be completed by early next 
year and the merger should be accomplished on july 1 1991 at 
least twothirds of the common stock must be tendered 
vista cannot solicit takeover proposals but the company may 
withdraw its recommendation of the tender offer and terminate the 
merger agreement if it receives a better proposal from a third 
party 
