expansion 
the deal would add 136000 electricity customers in kansas and 
colorado to utilicorps operations utilicorp based in kansas 
city provides gas and electric service to customers in eight 
states and british columbia 
the transaction requires approval from state and federal 
regulators 
we have had an interest in the centel property for some time 
because it enables us to further balance our electric and gas 
operations and our summer and winter peaking sources of revenue 
said utilicorp chairman and president richard c green jr 
chicagobased centel said in august that it wanted to sell its 
electricity properties to the highest bidder and concentrate on its 
telecommunications operations centel provides local exchange 
service to more than 16 million customers and operates cellular 
communications franchises in 15 states 
in kansas centel serves 65000 customers in dodge city 
concordia great bend and other communities in central and 
southwest kansas 
under the deal utilicorp will pay centel 2105 million in cash 
and pick up 213 million of centels liabilities 
in addition centels 8 percent interest in the jeffrey energy 
center in kansas will be picked up by a financial institution or 
insurance company for 114 million green said jeffrey comprises 
three coalfired generating plants 30 miles northwest of topeka 
utilicorp will pay 124 million a year to lease centels share 
of the facility at the end of 25 years utilicorp will recover 
centels interest in the facility at market value green said 
excluding the latest deal utilicorp has invested 4208 million 
in acquiring regulated utilities and 390 million to acquire 
unregulated properties since 1984 
