5518 billion sales had fallen 08 percent the previous month to 
5472 billion 
the activity pushed the ratio of inventoriestosales down to 
147 from 148 in september the ratio means it would take 147 
months to exhaust the backlog of goods at the october sales pace 
many economists do not consider a 147 ratio to be excessively 
high but a larger increase could be worrisome since a major rise 
in inventories in relation to sales could cause growing production 
cutbacks and job layoffs as businesses attempt to sell off the 
backlog 
even with the low inventory accumulation industrial production 
still fell 17 percent in november the federal reserve reported 
today at the same time 200000 factory jobs were lost that month 
