northwest airlines has become the fourth carrier 
to join a freebie war that is spreading through the sagging air 
travel industry 
northwests promotion parallels offers by other airlines but 
is the only one to include free travel to europe and hawaii the 
carrier said in a statement thursday 
delta air lines fired the opening salvo early this week 
offering free flights or firstclass upgrades to anybody who 
completes eight segments of travel 
a segment generally means any separate flight or connecting 
flight that costs more than a minimum amount 
late thursday american airlines and united airlines announced 
their own programs offering free flights to be taken later next 
year for anybody who racks up either eight segments of flight or 
three round trips 
american acknowledged its offer was in response to delta and 
united acknowledged it was responding to the other two 
northwests program also requires three roundtrips or eight 
segments spokeswoman christy clapp said this morning 
airlines typically rush to match cheap fares and promotions 
offered by their competitors for fear they could otherwise lose 
passengers 
analysts have said the latest deal seems to be getting a head 
start on promotions that generally come out after the winter 
holiday season as the sluggish months of january and february set 
in 
they said the airlines need to avoid offering broad deals that 
are too good for passengers or run the risk of compounding troubles 
brought on by high fuel prices and sluggish demand for air travel 
