<TEXT>
a us bankruptcy judge today turned down a 
federal agencys request for 45 more days to review the bankruptcy 
reorganization plan of southland corp the dallasbased owner of 
7eleven convenience stores 
judge harold abramson said the extension sought by the 
securities and exchange commission is too long for an opinion that 
is not required in the bankruptcy proceeding 
abramson had asked the sec for a statement about southlands 
prepackaged bankruptcy plan in which a creditorapproved 
blueprint for reemerging from bankruptcy reorganization is filed 
at the time a company seeks refuge from creditors ordinarily a 
company presents a reorganization plan months or even years later 
and creditors often challenge it 
the sec had wanted more time to prepare a statement saying 
southlands use of prepackaging would set a precedent for other 
large bankruptcy reorganizations and merited a lengthier review 
southland filed for bankruptcy protection in october using the 
prepackaging tool 
abramson said the sec has had months to look over southlands 
restructuring which he noted began in march 
i cant give you that long abramson told an sec attorney 
who asked for the 45day extension 
if the commission could make some kind of statement by dec 
31st or the first week of january that would be helpful to the 
court abramson said otherwise ill excuse you from that 
request 
the buck stops here anyway abramson said 
the judge indicated testimony in the southland confirmation 
hearing could last until early next month 
at the time of filing the company listed 253 billion in 
assets and 338 billion in liabilities and said it was overwhelmed 
by debt left from its 49 billion debtfinanced takeover in 1987 
southland which had sales of almost 8 billion last year is 
the largest of the few companies that have tried a prepackaged 
bankruptcy company officials believe prepackaging will allow the 
company to get out of the bankruptcy process in six months 
in addition to speeding up the bankruptcy process proponents of 
prepackaging say it assures a fairer deal for a greater number of 
creditors 
thats because a prepackaged plan must be approved by at least 
50 percent of the bondholders holding at least twothirds of a 
companys debt if a judge approves the terms of the plan are then 
imposed on the dissenting minority preventing holdouts from 
seeking better repayment terms 
southland in march said its japanese affiliates itoyokado co 
ltd and seveneleven japan co ltd were willing to spend 430 
million for stock in the reorganized company 
the terms of the prepackaged plan were agreed to in october 
just before the chapter 11 filing 
other companies notably atlantic city resorts owned by merv 
griffin and donald trump have used prepackaging in bankruptcy 
proceedings 
republic health corp a dallasbased owner of 14 hospitals 
filed a prepackaged chapter 11 plan last december and emerged from 
bankruptcy in april the company had posted a profit by the end of 
august 
