shortly after the first of the year the associated press will 
begin transmitting live data from its new financial markets 
computer system 
we are now conducting tests of the new system it is vital that 
each newspaper receiving digitalstocks dataspeed or slowspeed 
stocks wires participate in these tests 
for the past several weeks we have been sending test tables on 
sunday with advisories during the week telling members about the 
tests 
beginning next week dec 17 we will begin transmission of 
test data on a daily basis as well as sunday tests of the previous 
days tables will be transmitted at 2 am est weekly tests begin 
at noon on sundays 
checking the timeoffs is important in determining which 
transmissions are the test tables thats because the header 
information for the test tables is identical to headers for the 
regular tables again the test tables are those that arrive after 
2 am on weekdays and after noon on sunday 
the tests are for stocks bonds options and stockrelated 
summaries updown leaders what stocks did most active etc 
commodities and futures tables will be tested later so you wont 
see those tables now 
please ensure that the test transmissions are 1 captured 2 
typeset and 3 evaluated as soon as possible and 4 please let us 
know the results this is essential to a smooth transition to the 
new system 
although the tables are transmitted according to the same 
standards that have always applied it cannot be byteforbyte 
identical with data from the old computer system this especially 
applies to nonprinting spacing characters which may appear in a 
different sequence and tapevisible numbers 
if everything looks fine please advise your ap bureau chief if 
there are any problems setting the tables call or send the typeset 
copy quickly with an explanation to 
diane wright 
the associated press 
50 rockefeller plaza 
new york ny 10020 
212 6211568 
any questions about these tests or this advisory should be 
directed to ms wright at the above number many thanks for your 
cooperation 
