motorola inc will produce its next 
generation of computer memory chips in japan under a joint venture 
with japanese electronics manufacturer toshiba a spokesman said 
friday 
the fourmegabit dynamic random access memory chips will be 
manufactured at a factory in sendai japan that is coowned by 
motorola and toshiba rather than at motorolas new chip plant in 
austin texas said motorola spokesman dan rogers 
when production of the dynamic ram or dram chips begins in 
the third quarter of 1991 it will mark the first time motorola 
will offer that particular chip in large quantities rogers said 
the demand for faster computers has spurred a growing demand for 
another type of semiconductor static random access memory chips 
which are even faster than the dynamic ram chips to be produced in 
japan 
motorola based in this northwest chicago suburb decided to 
build the dynamic ram chips in japan and use its mos11 factory in 
austin to produce static ram chips beginning in 1992 the company 
said in a news release 
rapidly increasing demand worldwide for our fast static 
rams and microprocessors is straining our existing production 
capacity so mos11 will be used to meet this need said jim 
george vice president of motorolas mos memory products division 
in austin 
static ram chips are more expensive to produce but are four 
times faster than a dynamic ram chip of equal memory that speed 
makes the static ram chips desirable for computers used in the 
workplace an industry analyst said 
there is a definite demand for static rams which are 
potentially more profitable than dynamic rams the demand for that 
highspeed static ram is growing by leaps and bounds said 
millard phelps an analyst at the san francisco investment firm 
hambrecht amp quist 
motorola entered a longterm agreement with toshiba in 1986 to 
produce dynamic ram chips 
we are not going to be a leader in the dram industry the 
japanese have taken over that market rogers said thats why 
weve gone into a partnership agreement rather than going out on 
our own its a very expensive business to be in 
toshiba officials dismissed as speculation published reports 
that they pressured motorola into producing the dynamic ram chip in 
japan 
we never mentioned to motorola that toshiba didnt want 
motorola to produce the chip in the united states if motorola 
wanted to make the chip there it could have its their decision 
not ours said tedsou kadoya general manager of public 
communications for toshiba america inc 
motorola also produces computers pagers cellular phones 
twoway radios and defense and aerospace electronics 
