international paper co said friday it was 
charging 212 million against fourthquarter earnings for costs 
associated with scaling down operations and installating 
environmental controls 
the reserve fund is equal to 137 million after taxes or 126 
per share the company said international paper reported 546 
million in earnings or 501 per share in the first nine months 
of 1990 
international paper chairman john a georges said the sale and 
liquidation of company assets would improve the companys earnings 
and cash flow during and after 1991 
asset sales were expected to generate up to 200 million in 
aftertax proceeds over the next three years the company said 
international paper is a worldwide producer of paper and forest 
products with manufacturing operations in 22 countries 
the company did not identify which facilities and business units 
it was selling but said they either were not strategically 
important or not generating enough return on investment 
twothirds of the fourthquarter charge is to pay costs 
associated with the asset sales the company said the remainder is 
earmarked for paying for environmental controls at several 
woodtreating plants and for personnel costs associated with 
consolidation and improved productivity 
